            <td width="61%" align="center" valign="top"><a name="maincontent"></a> 
              <table width="98%" height="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" summary="layout table">
                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="title" --> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="maintitle"><strong>Sports Facilities &amp; Teams </strong></td>
                  <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></tr>
                <tr> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext">&nbsp; </td>
                </tr>
                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="main text" --> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext"> <span class="coursetitle"><strong>Facilities</strong></span>                    
                    <table width="100%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
                    <tr>
                      <td width="28%"><img src="images/science-lab.jpg" width="120" height="120"></td>
                      <td width="72%" class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Sports Science Laboratory </strong><br>
There is a fully equipped sports science laboratory and a separate nutrition and food preparation laboratory. These laboratories offer excellent facilities for physiology, including fitness testing, sport psychology practicals and dietary analysis and practical work with food.</font></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>                    
                    <table width="100%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="28%"><img src="images/gym.jpg" width="120" height="120"></td>
                        <td width="72%"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" class="bodytext"><strong>Fitness Suite</strong><br>
The fitness suite comprises of three treadmills, rowing machines, steppers and various cardiovascular equipment, in addition there are weight machines for multi-use. Students can become members of the fitness suite and have the opportunity to become qualified fitness instructors.</font></td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>                    
                    <table width="100%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="28%"><img src="images/tennis.jpg" width="120" height="120"></td>
                        <td width="72%" class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Squash &amp; Tennis / Netball Courts </strong><br>
There are four squash courts, including two glass-back courts with seating area, flood lit tennis and netball courts, all of which are used for practicals and student sport.</font></td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>                    
                    <table width="100%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="28%"><img src="images/football.jpg" width="120" height="120"></td>
                        <td width="72%" class="bodytext"><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Pitches<br>
                        </strong></font>We have several good quality grass pitches used for rugby and football and in the past these have been used by Leeds United Football Club for training purposes. Additionally there is a multi use floodlit training area. We also have access to local astro-turf pitches for lectures and student sport.</font></p>                        </td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>                    
                    <table width="100%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="28%" height="153"><img src="images/kids4.jpg" width="120" height="120"></td>
                        <td width="72%"><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" class="bodytext"><strong>Sports Hall<br>
                        </strong></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" class="bodytext">Students involved in teaching children from the local primary school during an activity afternoon as part of the level 1 module Children and Physical Activity.</font>
                          </p>
                        <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The sports hall is used for practical lectures and student sport and supports basketball, netball, indoor football, badminton and volleyball use. Students can book this facility through the sports office.</font></p></td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>                    
                    <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="sports_facilities_teams.htm">top</a></font>                    <hr>                    <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Teams </strong></font><font size="3" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><br>
                          <br>
                    </strong></font><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#football_m">Men&#8217;s Association Football</a></font><a href="#football_m"><font size="3" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong> </strong></font></a><font size="3" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><br>
                                    </strong></font><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#football_w">Women&#8217;s Association Football </a><br>
                                    <a href="#rugby_m">Men&#8217;s Rugby </a><br>
                                    <a href="#rugby_w">Women&#8217;s Rugby</a><br>
                                    <a href="#hockey">Hockey &#8211; Men&#8217;s and Women&#8217;s </a><br>
                                    <a href="#cricket">Cricket </a><br>
                                    <a href="#golf">Golf</a> <br>
                                    <a href="#netball">Netball </a><br>
                                    <a href="#volleyball">Men&#8217;s and Women&#8217;s Volleyball </a><br>
                                    <a href="#basketball">Men&#8217;s Basketball</a> </font><font size="3" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong> <br>
                                    </strong></font><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#badminton">Badminton</a></font><a href="#badminton"><font size="3" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong> </strong></font></a><font size="3" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><br>
                                    </strong></font><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#running">Running</a></font><br>
                  </p>                    
                  <hr>                    <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="football_m" id="football_m"></a>Men&#8217;s Association Football</strong><br>
                  Number of members: 50 - 70<br>
                  Approximate cost of joining: &pound;30 - &pound;35</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The Men&#8217;s Football Club is the largest sports club at the college. Every year the club attracts approximately 80 members and as such is able to operate 3 strong playing squads. The club competes in the BUSA competitions on Wednesdays and in the Northern University League on a weekend, the club will compete in Division One during the 2002/2003 season. Recent successes have seen the club finish 8th in the European University Football Championships in 1999 with the club also being crowned BUSA Plate champions in 1998. The club also has a proud tradition of end of season touring to continental destinations such as Barcelona (1998), Antwerp (1999) and Paris (2000). The club and all its existing members are looking forward to the footballing and the socializing that will prevail itself next season. </font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The club welcomes players of all abilities so why not come along and become one of the lads.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>                  
                  <hr>
                  <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="football_w"></a>Women&#8217;s Association Football<br>
                    </strong>Number of members: 15 - 20<br>
                    Approximate cost of joining: &pound;10</font></p>
                  <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The women&#8217;s football club continues to go from strength to strength with recent successes highlighting how far the club has grown since its reformation 5 years ago. The club competes in the BUSA competitions on a Wednesday and in the Northern Universities League at weekend. Recent successes have seen the club be BUSA quarter finalists for the past two seasons and runners up in the NUL last season. The club also has a proud tradition of touring with the girls regularly frequenting the shores of Blackpool on their end of season tours.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>                  
                  <hr>                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="rugby_m"></a>Men&#8217;s Rugby<br>
                  </strong>Number of members: 50 - 60<br>
                  Approximate cost of joining: &pound;25 -&pound;50 (Incl. T-shirt<br>
Shorts<br>
Sweatshirt (all initialed)<br>
Polo shirt<br>
Socks <br>
Tie</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The men&#8217;s rugby club is at present the most successful and prestigious club at college. The 1999/2000 season saw the club crowned as Yorkshire League Champions and Regional Divisional Champions and as such the club is now competing in the SRL National League, where last season it became the third most successful university side in the country. The club operates two teams, with the second team playing in the Yorkshire Alliance League. </font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> The social side of the club is renowned across all sports clubs, with the &#8216;social&#8217; being the highlight of the week for all club members. Concepts such as POWER HOUR and the FINING SESSIONS are an excellent chance to relax after a hard fought match. The club organises many trips including &#8220;Beer Bowling&#8221;, and &#8220;Mystery Days&#8221; where only a toothbrush and passport are required! However the main tour comes during the Easter break and the club has rumored that Prague, Germany or Italy are on the cards this year!</font></p>
                  <table width="100%"  border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5">
                    <tr>
                      <td width="27%"><img src="images/RFUcopy-2-small.jpg" alt="Copyright: Catholic Mission" width="108" height="95"></td>
                      <td width="73%"><p class="bodytext"><strong>Trinity &amp; All Saints "model" students feature in National Ad Campaign<br>
                      </strong>Five students from Leeds Trinity &amp; All Saints have featured in a national ad campaign for the Rugby Football union as part of their promotion for the 2005 Powergen Cup Final. <a href="http://www.leedstrinity.ac.uk/news/14-06-05-Rugby_union.htm">Read full story... </a></p></td>
                    </tr>
                  </table>                  <p class="bodytext">&nbsp;</p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>                  
                  <hr>
                  <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="rugby_w"></a>Women&#8217;s Rugby<br>
                    </strong>Number of members: 20</font></p>
                  <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The women&#8217;s rugby team has only recently reformed and have had successful seasons especially when you consider the relative inexperience of many of the girls. This season therefore the club is looking to build on last year&#8217;s foundation and start challenging for honors. The club also has a strong social side, especially on Wednesdays when the girls organise after match socials for members. The club welcomes both experienced and new rugby players and welcomes you into the fold this year.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>                  
                  <hr>                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="hockey"></a>Hockey &#8211; Men&#8217;s and Women&#8217;s<br>
                  </strong>Number of Members: 60<br>
                  Approximate cost of joining: Freshers &pound;40 including polo shirt,<br>
&pound;30 - 2nd and 3rd years</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The hockey clubs are looking forward to a successful season in 2002/2003. The club competes regularly in BUSA competition and arranges matches for players of all standards. Although competition is important, great emphasis is placed upon enjoyment of the sport and the social side of the club.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>                  
                  <hr>                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="cricket"></a>Cricket<br>
                  </strong>The cricket club re-launched a few years ago and has become a popular summertime club. A very dedicated and enthusiastic team, much of the emphasis is placed upon the social activities of the club.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>
                  <hr>                  <p class="bodytext"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="golf"></a></strong></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Golf<br>
                  </strong>The golf club has become very popular in recent years with the introduction of golf bursaries for single handicapped players. The club competes regularly in BUSA competitions and is open to players of all standards.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>                  
                  <hr>                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="volleyball"></a>Men&#8217;s and Women&#8217;s Volleyball<br>
                  </strong>There has been a men&#8217;s and women&#8217;s volleyball team entered into the BUSA leagues and a training time is scheduled. Therefore, if you are interested in playing volleyball or even taking a more active role like being captain, coach or chairperson, then let the Sports Office know.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>                  
                  <hr>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="basketball"></a>Men&#8217;s Basketball<br>
                    </strong>Men&#8217;s Basketball is one other sport that has taken a sideline over recent years. However, as with volleyball a basketball team has been entered into the BUSA leagues, a coach has been drafted in from an organised basketball club, and a training time has been reserved. Therefore, if you are interested in taking part and playing basketball this year then call into the Sports Office and we will point you in the right direction.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>
                  <hr>                  <p class="bodytext"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a name="badminton"></a></strong></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong>Badminton<br>
                  </strong>There is an external friendly non-league badminton club that comes to TASC on Friday evenings 7.30 &#8211; 9.30, who are looking for new players and will welcome any new comers with open arms.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>
                  <hr>                  <p class="bodytext"><strong><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a name="running"></a>Running<br>
                  </font></strong><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">For a number of years (actually for as long as I can remember) there has been an unofficial running club that runs on Tuesdays 1.00 &#8211; 2.00pm. The Sports Office hopes that this will continue again this year, hoping to capture or nurture new talent to either take part in various events around the county, or may be to take it further and join the prestigious clubs within Leeds.</font></p>
                  <p class="bodytext"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="#top">top</a></font></p>                  
                  <p>&nbsp;</p></td>
